# Force LF in the working tree on every platform. The toolchain expects LF
# everywhere — rustfmt (`newline_style = "Unix"`), taplo, and `.editorconfig`.
# Without this, Git's `core.autocrlf=true` (the Windows default) checks files out
# as CRLF, so formatting checks and Lefthook can fail on a native Windows host
# even though the repository blobs are LF.
# `text=auto` still lets Git auto-detect and leave binaries alone.
#
# Existing Windows clones: after pulling this file, run once to refresh the working
# tree to LF:  git add --renormalize . && git checkout .
* text=auto eol=lf

# Archive and codec binaries — never normalize these.
*.tar binary
*.tgz binary
*.cpio binary
*.ar binary
*.a binary
*.zip binary
*.7z binary
*.iso binary
*.gz binary
*.zst binary
*.xz binary
*.lz4 binary
*.bin binary
*.exe binary
*.pdb binary

# Frozen fuzz-corpus seeds and any test fixtures are compared byte-exact; keep them
# byte-identical on every platform (never rewrite LF <-> CRLF inside them).
fuzz/corpus/** -text
**/tests/fixtures/** -text
